Today’s Day 41 “Road to Fluent Spanish” session focused heavily on practical real-world restaurant Spanish, conversational confidence, and continued reinforcement of foundational Unit 1 Pimsleur concepts. Duolingo introduced several useful conversational phrases and restaurant-related vocabulary, while Memrise reinforced common descriptive and food-related words such as “mercado,” “rápido,” “edificio,” “gordo,” and “enfermo.” Additional emphasis was placed on phrases the user plans to actively use tonight at a local Mexican restaurant, including asking for recommendations, ordering politely, requesting water, asking to practice Spanish, and handling basic small talk naturally with restaurant staff.

The weekly key conversational phrases were reviewed again, with noticeably improved recall and fluency compared to earlier in the week. Core travel and restaurant phrases such as “¿Dónde está la puerta de embarque?”, “¿A qué hora sale el vuelo?”, “¿Qué me recomiendas del menú?”, “La cuenta, por favor,” and “Es mi primera vez aquí” are becoming much more automatic. The user also demonstrated stronger understanding of practical ordering phrases like “Voy a pedir una quesadilla…” and “Quiero arroz y frijoles también.”

Pimsleur Unit 1 review continued with Lessons 23 and 24. Major focus areas included:

directions and navigation
“por aquí” vs “por allí”
formal vs informal commands
nearby/far expressions
“Creo que…” sentence structures
speaking/listening confidence
remembering phrases involving leaving/traveling
Several corrections were reinforced:

“Todo está cerrado” instead of “Todos están cerrado”
“Me gusta practicar mi español” instead of “practicando”
“una quesadilla” instead of “un quesadilla”
“Sí, todo está muy bueno” instead of “todos es buenos”
The user also practiced realistic waiter/customer interactions, improving response speed and natural phrasing for restaurant conversations. Overall fluency and conversational comfort continue improving, especially in practical travel and dining situations that will directly apply to the upcoming Puerto Rico trip.
